<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6145021636704338877">Richard Lloyd Parry was born in north-west England, and has lived since 1995 in Tokyo, where he is the Asia Editor of The Times newspaper of London. He has reported from twenty-eight countries, including Afghanistan, Iraq and North Korea. In 2005, he was named the UK&apos;s foreign correspondent of the year. He has also written for Granta, the New York Times and the London Review of Books.</span>
  <span id="freeText6145021636704338877" style="display:none">Richard Lloyd Parry was born in north-west England, and has lived since 1995 in Tokyo, where he is the Asia Editor of The Times newspaper of London. He has reported from twenty-eight countries, including Afghanistan, Iraq and North Korea. In 2005, he was named the UK's foreign correspondent of the year. He has also written for Granta, the New York Times and the London Review of Books.</span>
